      {
        "introduction": "Ahaz must surely consider Isaiah a crazy dreamer. He probably does not even begin to understand Isaiah's message regarding the coming Messiah. Moreover, he does not have enough faith in God to believe that he could actually defeat Israel and Syria (and even Assyria, if necessary) simply by trusting God. Foolishly, Ahaz will trust his own military strength instead.\n\nSo having rejected God's support and having ignored Isaiah's warnings, Ahaz joins in battle against Pekah and Rezin. The historical account records the predictable results."
